FBIS4-36412 "drnes111_j_94015" FBIS-NES-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Salih Receives UK Ambassador, Support for Unity Salih Receives UK Ambassador, Support for Unity JN0806141694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 8 Jun 94 JN0806141694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, Presidential Council chairman, today received UK Ambassador Robert Douglas Gordon. They reviewed bilateral relations and the developments of the situation in our country, as well as issues of interest to the two countries. During the meeting, the British ambassador reiterated the United Kingdom's support for Yemeni unity and democracy, and its eagerness to promote its relations with the Republic of Yemen in all fields in the service of the two friendly countries' common interests. The brother chairman of the Presidential Council expressed appreciation for the British stand supporting unity and democracy. He stressed that this stand genuinely reflects British interest in consolidating security and stability in Yemen and the region. He stressed our country's eagerness to promote its relations with Britain and to expand the spheres of cooperation. He indicated that Yemeni-British relations will witness further development and prosperity. The meeting was attended by Foreign Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah.
